1
00:00:02,627 --> 00:00:04,393
♪

2
00:00:05,780 --> 00:00:07,764
♪

3
00:01:05,474 --> 00:01:07,518
NARRATOR: <i>Previously on</i> Superman:

4
00:01:07,542 --> 00:01:09,154
Great Darkseid.

5
00:01:09,178 --> 00:01:11,990
<i>The reprogramming is a complete success.</i>

6
00:01:12,014 --> 00:01:14,425
He will attack Earth as I planned?

7
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:17,628
GRANNY: <i>Yes, uniting that planet's military force</i>

8
00:01:17,652 --> 00:01:19,164
<i>to destroy him.</i>

9
00:01:19,188 --> 00:01:20,698
What's happened to you?

10
00:01:20,722 --> 00:01:22,834
I don't know.

11
00:01:22,858 --> 00:01:23,890
HARDCASTLE: Fire!

12
00:01:25,426 --> 00:01:28,027
Nothing could've survived that.

13
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:33,332
♪

14
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:40,139
[SIREN WAILING]

15
00:01:43,011 --> 00:01:44,744
[COUGHS]

16
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:50,917
[COUGHING]

17
00:02:00,929 --> 00:02:02,106
Superman!

18
00:02:02,130 --> 00:02:03,842
Stay back.

19
00:02:03,866 --> 00:02:04,866
Lois?

20
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:07,595
Where are you taking them?

21
00:02:07,619 --> 00:02:09,085
Lois.

22
00:02:13,207 --> 00:02:14,651
[LAUGHS]

23
00:02:14,675 --> 00:02:17,138
Come to Granny, darling.

24
00:02:17,162 --> 00:02:20,596
She'll make it all better.

25
00:02:34,512 --> 00:02:36,412
[GRUNTING]

26
00:02:39,317 --> 00:02:40,317
[SCREAMS]

27
00:02:47,025 --> 00:02:48,336
GRANNY: Bring him here.

28
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,839
Great Darkseid has something special

29
00:02:50,863 --> 00:02:52,090
planned for this one.

30
00:02:52,114 --> 00:02:53,808
[GRUNTS]

31
00:02:53,832 --> 00:02:54,832
[SCREAMING]

32
00:03:00,505 --> 00:03:04,102
Welcome, Kal-El, my son.

33
00:03:04,126 --> 00:03:05,492
[GASPS]

34
00:03:09,464 --> 00:03:10,541
[DOOR OPENS]

35
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:11,943
HARDCASTLE: Gotta thank Luthor

36
00:03:11,967 --> 00:03:13,611
for those red sun lamps.

37
00:03:13,635 --> 00:03:15,185
They sure even things up.

38
00:03:17,272 --> 00:03:19,951
The only reason you're being kept alive

39
00:03:19,975 --> 00:03:21,536
is to tell us what's going on.

40
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,288
I don't know.

41
00:03:23,312 --> 00:03:25,256
Then let me bring you up to date.

42
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,775
You're a military prisoner about to stand trial

43
00:03:27,799 --> 00:03:30,228
for your traitorous attack on Earth.

44
00:03:30,252 --> 00:03:31,212
Sound familiar?

45
00:03:31,236 --> 00:03:33,097
I wasn't responsible.

46
00:03:33,121 --> 00:03:35,183
Of course not.

47
00:03:35,207 --> 00:03:36,673
Where's Super Girl?

48
00:03:37,809 --> 00:03:38,858
Let's go.

49
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:46,027
MAN [OVER SPEAKER]: <i>The crisis has passed,</i>

50
00:03:46,051 --> 00:03:47,795
<i>and the threat of hostile alien invasion</i>

51
00:03:47,819 --> 00:03:49,280
<i>has been neutralized.</i>

52
00:03:49,304 --> 00:03:50,264
[MURMURING]

53
00:03:50,288 --> 00:03:51,783
Superman's dead?

54
00:03:51,807 --> 00:03:55,091
<i>I repeat, the threat has been neutralized.</i>

55
00:03:55,744 --> 00:03:56,771
That's not true.

56
00:03:56,795 --> 00:03:58,589
He was alive when he was taken away.

57
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:01,008
Where are you holding him? And where's Super Girl?

58
00:04:01,032 --> 00:04:03,294
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, thank you for your time.</i>

59
00:04:03,318 --> 00:04:04,433
You didn't answer me!

60
00:04:06,004 --> 00:04:07,536
Answer me!

61
00:04:09,057 --> 00:04:11,569
First you declare all-out war on Earth,

62
00:04:11,593 --> 00:04:13,170
and now that you've lost,

63
00:04:13,194 --> 00:04:14,255
you'd like us to believe

64
00:04:14,279 --> 00:04:18,447
an alien despot was controlling your mind.

65
00:04:19,618 --> 00:04:22,597
How stupid do you think we are?

66
00:04:22,621 --> 00:04:24,532
Darkseid's attacked Earth before.

67
00:04:24,556 --> 00:04:26,684
He wants this planet any way he can get it.

68
00:04:26,708 --> 00:04:29,354
And how do we know you haven't been in league with him?

69
00:04:29,378 --> 00:04:31,622
I swear to you that I was manipulated.

70
00:04:31,646 --> 00:04:34,692
Just following orders. Hm, is that it?

71
00:04:34,716 --> 00:04:35,759
Believe me,

72
00:04:35,783 --> 00:04:37,495
I'll do anything within my power

73
00:04:37,519 --> 00:04:39,030
to make it right.

74
00:04:39,054 --> 00:04:40,864
To who, Superman?

75
00:04:40,888 --> 00:04:44,786
You betrayed us poor earthlings, attacked us in cold blood.

76
00:04:44,810 --> 00:04:46,804
How would you win back our trust?

77
00:04:46,828 --> 00:04:48,588
Rescue a kitten from a tree?

78
00:04:50,649 --> 00:04:53,116
Take him back to his cell.

79
00:04:53,985 --> 00:04:55,000
[GRUNTING]

80
00:05:04,529 --> 00:05:06,274
I'm here from Washington.

81
00:05:06,298 --> 00:05:07,975
Security clearance alpha.

82
00:05:07,999 --> 00:05:09,994
♪

83
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:11,551
[BEEPING]

84
00:05:14,572 --> 00:05:17,374
That's one plus of having a father in the Pentagon.

85
00:05:27,119 --> 00:05:30,119
GUARD: See how the mighty have fallen.

86
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:35,336
Still think you can take us weak,

87
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,009
little earthlings, big man?

88
00:05:42,901 --> 00:05:44,501
[GRUNTS] [GRUNTS]

89
00:05:49,674 --> 00:05:51,652
[ALARM BEEPING]

90
00:05:51,676 --> 00:05:53,476
[COUGHING]

91
00:05:58,532 --> 00:06:00,816
Nice try, traitor.

92
00:06:11,446 --> 00:06:15,181
If he tries that again, alert me, immediately.

93
00:06:17,802 --> 00:06:19,163
I told you.

94
00:06:19,187 --> 00:06:22,050
Superman's too dangerous to keep locked up here.

95
00:06:22,074 --> 00:06:23,568
I agree, Lex.

96
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:27,204
If he or Super Girl should escape, they'd be unstoppable.

97
00:06:27,228 --> 00:06:28,973
A threat to all mankind.

98
00:06:28,997 --> 00:06:31,897
There's only one permanent solution.

99
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:47,421
♪

100
00:06:53,062 --> 00:06:54,707
So it ends like this.

101
00:06:54,731 --> 00:06:57,609
Don't think of it as an end, Superman.

102
00:06:57,633 --> 00:07:01,497
My biotech people will spend years studying your carcass.

103
00:07:01,521 --> 00:07:06,123
I'm certain it will be a most profitable endeavor.

104
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:10,122
Now that I'm as normal as you, Lex,

105
00:07:10,146 --> 00:07:12,346
I wonder if you'd grant me one last request.

106
00:07:14,634 --> 00:07:16,000
And that is?

107
00:07:18,287 --> 00:07:19,287
[GRUNTS]

108
00:07:20,123 --> 00:07:21,366
Thank you.

109
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:23,007
Filthy alien.

110
00:07:33,436 --> 00:07:34,902
[GRUNTS]

111
00:07:36,606 --> 00:07:38,556
What in blazes...? [GRUNTS]

112
00:07:42,478 --> 00:07:44,145
[YELLING]

113
00:07:49,084 --> 00:07:50,061
Lois!

114
00:07:50,085 --> 00:07:51,497
What are you doing here?

115
00:07:51,521 --> 00:07:53,954
Have you ever tried to get a story out of the military?

116
00:07:55,891 --> 00:07:58,692
I figured it'd be easier to go straight to the source.

117
00:08:03,282 --> 00:08:05,076
Security alert.

118
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,528
Sector three.

119
00:08:06,552 --> 00:08:08,169
[ALARM BLARING]

120
00:08:13,176 --> 00:08:14,675
[BOTH GRUNTING & COUGHING]

121
00:08:19,164 --> 00:08:21,197
We can get out this way.

122
00:08:21,984 --> 00:08:23,412
Not without Super Girl.

123
00:08:23,436 --> 00:08:25,653
Nothing's ever easy with you, is it?

124
00:08:33,746 --> 00:08:35,379
This way.

125
00:08:38,701 --> 00:08:41,313
Kara!

126
00:08:41,337 --> 00:08:42,619
[POUNDING]

127
00:08:44,823 --> 00:08:46,573
I'm not talking to you.

128
00:08:48,544 --> 00:08:50,656
Listen, they wanna kill you.

129
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:53,642
You have to get out now.

130
00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:55,911
Can't.

131
00:08:55,935 --> 00:08:57,579
Feel so weak.

132
00:08:57,603 --> 00:08:58,580
It's the red lights.

133
00:08:58,604 --> 00:09:00,587
Stand back.

134
00:09:15,754 --> 00:09:19,018
You've got some serious explaining to do.

135
00:09:19,042 --> 00:09:20,819
Later. We've gotta get out of here.

136
00:09:20,843 --> 00:09:21,843
[SCREAMS]

137
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:39,526
She needs a doctor. Fast.

138
00:09:51,857 --> 00:09:52,857
[ALL YELLING]

139
00:10:10,142 --> 00:10:12,326
Hang on tight.

140
00:10:29,028 --> 00:10:30,127
[EKG BEEPING]

141
00:10:33,032 --> 00:10:34,464
[BUZZING]

142
00:10:43,058 --> 00:10:45,058
♪

143
00:10:56,672 --> 00:10:57,688
[DOOR OPENS]

144
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:06,125
I'm sorry, Superman. There's nothing I can do.

145
00:11:06,149 --> 00:11:07,709
Emil, she'll die.

146
00:11:07,733 --> 00:11:08,876
But if I help either of you,

147
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,895
it'd be considered an act of treason.

148
00:11:10,919 --> 00:11:11,880
[GASPS]

149
00:11:11,904 --> 00:11:13,114
Hamilton.

150
00:11:13,138 --> 00:11:14,271
[GRUNTING]

151
00:11:15,408 --> 00:11:17,891
Yes, of course. Just don't hurt me.

152
00:11:23,749 --> 00:11:25,210
I'm sorry.

153
00:11:25,234 --> 00:11:27,567
Please, do what you can.

154
00:11:34,844 --> 00:11:36,577
Superman, wait!

155
00:11:39,681 --> 00:11:41,827
Did you see the look on Hamilton's face?

156
00:11:41,851 --> 00:11:43,579
He'll never trust me again.

157
00:11:43,603 --> 00:11:45,530
He doesn't understand.

158
00:11:45,554 --> 00:11:48,867
Frankly, I'm having trouble piecing it together myself.

159
00:11:48,891 --> 00:11:50,252
What happened to you?

160
00:11:50,276 --> 00:11:52,108
It was Darkseid.

161
00:11:53,779 --> 00:11:55,657
He stripped away my memory,

162
00:11:55,681 --> 00:11:58,427
turned me loose to destroy everything I've ever loved.

163
00:11:58,451 --> 00:12:02,263
First the invasion of Earth, then the murder of Dan Turpin.

164
00:12:02,287 --> 00:12:06,507
Now Super Girl's life is hanging by a thread, and I'm an outcast.

165
00:12:10,796 --> 00:12:13,096
Darkseid's responsible for all of it.

166
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:15,760
What are you gonna do?

167
00:12:15,784 --> 00:12:18,513
Settle it.

168
00:12:18,537 --> 00:12:19,937
Once and for all.

169
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:26,293
Wait!

170
00:12:42,127 --> 00:12:43,276
Heaven help you.

171
00:12:53,763 --> 00:12:55,629
[ALL GROWLING]

172
00:12:56,766 --> 00:12:58,766
♪

173
00:13:11,064 --> 00:13:13,008
Father, it's Superman.

174
00:13:13,032 --> 00:13:16,528
So the prodigal son returns.

175
00:13:16,552 --> 00:13:18,552
Let him come.

176
00:13:22,458 --> 00:13:23,557
[CRASH] Huh?

177
00:13:28,581 --> 00:13:29,581
[SCREAMS]

178
00:13:31,267 --> 00:13:33,150
You're first on my list.

179
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,581
A joke.

180
00:13:35,605 --> 00:13:38,918
It was only a joke, my little sugar drop.

181
00:13:38,942 --> 00:13:40,419
I'm not laughing.

182
00:13:40,443 --> 00:13:42,922
Now, now. Don't be cross.

183
00:13:42,946 --> 00:13:45,379
Let Granny make everything better.

184
00:13:46,232 --> 00:13:48,849
[SCREAMS] Ungrateful brat!

185
00:13:50,152 --> 00:13:52,748
I gave you a glorious new life.

186
00:13:52,772 --> 00:13:56,823
And now you turn on dear, old Granny?

187
00:13:59,862 --> 00:14:02,191
[LAUGHING]

188
00:14:02,215 --> 00:14:03,642
[GRUNTING]

189
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:06,345
Well, this time I won't leave you

190
00:14:06,369 --> 00:14:08,785
wits enough to pick your... No!

191
00:14:09,988 --> 00:14:10,988
[SCREAMING]

192
00:14:13,409 --> 00:14:14,491
[GRUNTS]

193
00:14:15,812 --> 00:14:17,061
[SCREAMING]

194
00:14:23,269 --> 00:14:24,585
Sweet dreams.

195
00:14:33,780 --> 00:14:35,257
Welcome back, lover.

196
00:14:35,281 --> 00:14:37,259
Give us a kiss?

197
00:14:37,283 --> 00:14:38,916
Get out of my way, Lashina.

198
00:14:46,292 --> 00:14:47,292
[LAUGHING]

199
00:14:48,293 --> 00:14:50,093
Tag, you're it!

200
00:14:57,303 --> 00:14:59,698
Ain't that a kick in the head?

201
00:14:59,722 --> 00:15:02,239
Wanna play footsie?

202
00:15:04,727 --> 00:15:08,123
I'm not finished with you, boy toy.

203
00:15:08,147 --> 00:15:09,196
Yes, you are.

204
00:15:25,248 --> 00:15:27,881
[MUFFLED BANGING]

205
00:15:32,588 --> 00:15:34,605
♪

206
00:15:47,186 --> 00:15:48,664
[THUD]

207
00:15:48,688 --> 00:15:50,666
I can't believe he's blood.

208
00:15:50,690 --> 00:15:52,067
You used me.

209
00:15:52,091 --> 00:15:54,436
I told you once, Superman,

210
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:56,171
if you would not be my knight,

211
00:15:56,195 --> 00:15:57,756
you would be my pawn.

212
00:15:57,780 --> 00:15:59,842
I see you're a man of your word.

213
00:15:59,866 --> 00:16:02,010
I am many things, Kal-El.

214
00:16:02,034 --> 00:16:04,429
You couldn't begin to imagine half of them.

215
00:16:04,453 --> 00:16:08,338
But for now, I shall take the role of executioner.

216
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:10,257
[GRUNTING]

217
00:16:11,377 --> 00:16:14,078
A final gift, my wayward son.

218
00:16:18,051 --> 00:16:19,728
A fast death.

219
00:16:19,752 --> 00:16:21,630
Infinitely preferable to the shame

220
00:16:21,654 --> 00:16:22,865
of returning to Earth.

221
00:16:22,889 --> 00:16:24,833
There, your legacy would be one

222
00:16:24,857 --> 00:16:26,535
of fear and distrust.

223
00:16:26,559 --> 00:16:29,705
A pariah desperately chasing the favor of a world

224
00:16:29,729 --> 00:16:32,129
that cursed your name.

225
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,213
You dare strike me?

226
00:17:12,822 --> 00:17:14,205
[ALL SCREAMING]

227
00:17:20,196 --> 00:17:22,091
That's for Dan Turpin.

228
00:17:22,115 --> 00:17:23,074
Who?

229
00:17:23,098 --> 00:17:24,760
The good man you murdered.

230
00:17:24,784 --> 00:17:27,595
Had I known one human's death would pain you so,

231
00:17:27,619 --> 00:17:29,186
I would have killed more.

232
00:17:38,363 --> 00:17:39,742
And kill more I shall.

233
00:17:39,766 --> 00:17:43,333
Carry<i> that</i> agony with you to oblivion, Superman.

234
00:17:50,143 --> 00:17:51,191
[ALL SCREAMING]

235
00:18:45,414 --> 00:18:47,248
[GRUNTS]

236
00:18:53,439 --> 00:18:55,239
[ALL GASP]

237
00:19:02,265 --> 00:19:03,580
[THUD]

238
00:19:15,127 --> 00:19:17,155
Darkseid is finished.

239
00:19:17,179 --> 00:19:18,662
Do with him as you will.

240
00:19:19,732 --> 00:19:20,931
You're free.

241
00:19:25,303 --> 00:19:26,280
Master.

242
00:19:26,304 --> 00:19:28,116
Let me help you, master.

243
00:19:28,140 --> 00:19:29,990
Gently. Be careful.

244
00:19:37,716 --> 00:19:39,778
I am many things, Kal-El,

245
00:19:39,802 --> 00:19:43,987
but here, I am god.

246
00:19:51,029 --> 00:19:53,157
GIRL: Don't, Clark.

247
00:19:53,181 --> 00:19:55,127
Kara.

248
00:19:55,151 --> 00:19:58,981
You fight by Darkseid's rules, you're gonna kill somebody.

249
00:19:59,005 --> 00:20:00,365
And it won't be him.

250
00:20:00,389 --> 00:20:02,122
Let it go.

251
00:20:05,645 --> 00:20:07,061
Let's go home.

252
00:20:08,414 --> 00:20:10,125
Home.

253
00:20:10,149 --> 00:20:12,928
In the wake of this week's dramatic developments,

254
00:20:12,952 --> 00:20:14,379
we asked the people of Metropolis

255
00:20:14,403 --> 00:20:16,848
how they felt about the Man of Steel.

256
00:20:16,872 --> 00:20:17,966
If you ask me,

257
00:20:17,990 --> 00:20:20,769
the bum oughta go back where he came from.

258
00:20:20,793 --> 00:20:24,606
I used to consider him my friend, but now...

259
00:20:24,630 --> 00:20:27,425
Superman saved the world dozens of times.

260
00:20:27,449 --> 00:20:29,528
We owe him a second chance.

261
00:20:29,552 --> 00:20:32,781
No one man should have that much power.

262
00:20:32,805 --> 00:20:35,372
HARDCASTLE: <i>He's a traitor and a menace.</i>

263
00:20:36,909 --> 00:20:39,229
WOMAN: <i>I'm locking my bedroom door at night.</i>

264
00:20:40,746 --> 00:20:42,123
LOIS: Don't listen to them.

265
00:20:42,147 --> 00:20:45,193
No, they're right.

266
00:20:45,217 --> 00:20:47,728
I did lose control, and it scares me.

267
00:20:47,752 --> 00:20:48,847
If I can't trust myself,

268
00:20:48,871 --> 00:20:52,372
how can I win back the trust of an entire planet?

269
00:21:02,901 --> 00:21:04,384
One person at a time.

270
00:21:14,053 --> 00:21:16,053
♪

